<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880622-0163 </DOCNO><HL> Treasury Plans to Sell $12.8 Billion of Bills </HL><SO> </SO><IN> BON FIN </IN><G> TRE </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Treasury said it plans to raise about $175 million in new cash with the sale Monday of about $12.8 billion in short-term bills for $12.64 billion in maturing bills.    The offering will be divided evenly between 13-week and 26-week bills maturing on Sept. 29 and Dec. 29, respectively.    Tenders for the bills, available in minimum $10,000 denominations, must be received by 1 p.m. EDT Monday at the Treasury or at Federal Reserve banks or branches. </TEXT></DOC>